<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<pretext xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <ns0:include href="../docinfo.ptx" />
  <article>
    
    <worksheet margin="1in" bottom="1.25in" xml:id="ws-series">
      <title>Worksheet for Section 8.2</title>

      <objectives>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              Identify convergent and divergent series.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Know the definition of a convergent series.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p> Use the geometric series formulas <m>\sum_{k=0}^{n-1}ar^k=a\frac{1-r^n}{1-r}</m> and <m>\sum_{k=0}^\infty
              ar^k=\frac{a}{1-r}</m> when <m>r &lt; 1</m>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </objectives>


      <page>
        <exercisegroup>
          <title>Testing for convergence</title>
          <introduction>
            <p>
              Determine the convergence or divergence of each of the following series. If the series
              converges, try to find the sum.
            </p>
          </introduction>

          <exercise workspace="1in">
            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n = 1}^\infty \tan n</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
            </exercise>

          <exercise workspace="1in">
            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n = 1}^\infty \frac{n+1}{2n - 3}</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
            </exercise>

          <exercise workspace="1in">
            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n = 1}^\infty \ln\left( \frac{n}{n+1} \right)</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
            </exercise>

        </exercisegroup>

        <exercise workspace="1in">
          <introduction>
            <p> Let <m>\left\{a_n\right\}</m> be an increasing sequence such that <m>a_1 &gt;0</m>
              and <m>a_n
                \leq 100</m> for all <m>n \geq 1</m>. </p>
          </introduction>
          <task>
            <statement>
              <p> Does the sequence <m>\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n</m> converge? </p>
            </statement>

            </task>
          <task>
            <statement>
              <p> Does the series <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty a_n</m> converge? </p>
            </statement>
            </task>
        </exercise>
      </page>
      <page>
        <exercise workspace="1in">
          <statement>
            <p>
              Suppose that the country of Pottsylvania spends $2 billion and that each recipient of
              a fraction of this wealth spends 90% of the dollars that he or she receives. In turn,
              the secondary recipients spend 90% of the dollars that they receive, and so on. What
              is the total spending that results from the original injection of $2 billion dollars
              into the economy?
            </p>
          </statement>

          </exercise>

        <exercise workspace="1in">
          <statement>
            <p> Express <m>6.254254\ldots</m> as a ratio of two integers. </p>
          </statement>

          </exercise>

        <exercise workspace="1in">
          <statement>
            <p>
              A ball is dropped from a height of 6 ft. Each time the ball bounces, it comes back up
              to one-half of its previous height. What is the total distance that the ball travels?
            </p>
          </statement>
          </exercise>
      </page>
    </worksheet>
  </article>
